# Common Problems

## Socket does not exist

Cause

Gunicorn failed.

Check

```
sudo journalctl -u recruiter
```

---

## Permission denied creating socket

Do **not** bind directly to

```
/run/recruiter.sock
```

Use

```
RuntimeDirectory=recruiter
```

and

```
/run/recruiter/gunicorn.sock
```

---

## curl --unix-socket fails

Gunicorn is not running.

Verify

```
sudo systemctl status recruiter
```

---

## 502 Bad Gateway

Usually means

* Gunicorn stopped
* Wrong socket path
* Nginx points to the wrong socket

---

## 404 Not Found

Usually means

* Wrong Django URL configuration
* Wrong project module
* Incorrect WSGI application path

---

## 522 Cloudflare

Cloudflare cannot reach your server.

Check

* DNS records
* AWS Security Group
* UFW
* Nginx listening on ports 80 and 443

---

## Could not resolve host

DNS record missing.

Example

```
A recruiter -> Public IP
```

---

## SSL certificate file missing

```
cannot load certificate
```

Certificate has not been generated.

Run

```
sudo certbot --nginx
```

---

## Invalid number of arguments in http2 directive

Use

```
listen 443 ssl;
http2 on;
```

Do not use deprecated or incorrect combinations for your installed Nginx version.

---

## listen ... http2 directive is deprecated

Use

```
listen 443 ssl;
http2 on;
```

instead of

```
listen 443 ssl http2;
```

if your installed Nginx version recommends the newer syntax.

